						               													<description>Kruiswoordspel is a game for &amp;quot;2 or more&amp;quot; players in which words are formed from 13 dice with letters on them. The slogan in English is &amp;quot;Fun With Letters&amp;quot;. On each player's turn, they roll the dice using the provided cup, and try to form as many interconnected words as possible from the top-facing letters, before the provided sand timer runs out (approximately 4 minutes). Point values of the used letters are added up (double-counting any that are used in two words), and the values of any unused letters are subtracted. Any disputed words are settled by the player who went first, the &amp;quot;leader&amp;quot; - either by looking it up in a dictionary of his/her choice, or &amp;quot;deciding himself&amp;quot; whether to accept the word. After a &amp;quot;prearranged number of rounds&amp;quot;, the player with the highest total score is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Differences from the more-well-known Scrabble Crossword Cubes game include:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     13 dice rather than 14&amp;#10;     different combinations of letters on them (e.g. all dice have a mixture of vowels and consonants on them, vs most of the vowels being together on four dice that have no consonants)&amp;#10;     different points values (e.g. F=3 vs 4, H=2 vs 4, K=4 vs 5, V=3 vs 4, X=6 vs 8)&amp;#10;     dispute resolution is not necessarily based on a standard dictionary&amp;#10;     types of words to be excluded are not specified&amp;#10;     Scrabble Crossword Cubes includes a second set of rules in which words of specific lengths must be spelled&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
